OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1778785872
OL,3,CPrince Harry speaks out on 'deeply
OL,4,Ctroubling' rise of antisemitism in UK
OL,6,F"We have seen how legitimate protest
OL,7,Fagainst state actions in the Middle
OL,8,FEast does exist alongside hostility
OL,9,Ftoward Jewish communities at home `
OL,10,Fjust as we have also seen how
OL,11,Fcriticism of those actions can be too
OL,12,Feasily dismissed or mischaracterised,"
OL,13,FHarry wrote.
OL,15,F"Nothing, whether criticism of a
OL,16,Fgovernment or the reality of violence
OL,17,Fand destruction, can ever justify
OL,18,Fhostility toward an entire people or
OL,19,Ffaith."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1778785872
OL,3,CPrince Harry speaks out on 'deeply
OL,4,Ctroubling' rise of antisemitism in UK
OL,6,FThe duke noted that there was "deep
OL,7,Fand justified alarm" at the scale of
OL,8,Floss in Gaza and Lebanon, but argued
OL,9,Fpeople must be more "clear" about who
OL,10,Ftheir anger is directed at.
OL,12,FBut while he referenced the actions of
OL,13,F"the state" throughout, he did not
OL,14,Fname Israel during the article.
OL,26,@nD@_OUoD@TO]qD@UOUqD@[O]uD@AOUuD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
